		<div class="why">
			<center><h3>Why this topic?</h3></center>
			<p>We chose to do create our website based on this topic because too many young undocumented immigrants are conditioned to believe that their legal status determines their educational opportunities. Nearly 61% of undocumented immigrants lack a high school diploma, with just 25% graduating high school, 5% completing some college, and only 9% becoming college graduates. Yet, there is hope to collectively change this reality. We can do our part to make scholarships better known to those who need them. We feel that undocumented youth immigrants should have the same educational opportunities available as every other youth.  </p>
